URL reference: https://kubernetes.io/blog/2026/04/23/kubernetes-v1-36-userns-ga/
DateReviewed: 2026-05-16
Description: Our article today dives into user namespaces finally going GA in Kubernetes v1.36. We start with background - this has been in the pipe for a long time, and it's foundational to getting to true rootless security. The basic idea is inside the container the process looks like root; but in the host process system, it's an unprivledged user. It allows access to privledged system calls, but only in the context of the container. Previously, if you needed to make a priv. system call, you had to be root on the host or it would fail; no uid 0, no success. Not anymore. This also extends to volumes - at first, kubelet would chown all the files, but now, the kernel remaps them at mount time. They even have a short example with YAML.
BottomLine: Good piece on User Namespaces and how they help in Kubernetes
